Toy-maker Fisher-Price is recalling 83 toys, including Big Bird and Elmo, due to lead paint.
This follows a similar move by RC2 Corp. Mattel apologized for the recall, affecting nearly a million toys.
The issue was detected internally and reported to the Consumer Product Safety Commission.
The company aims to improve procedures and regain trust.
Concerns over Chinese-made products have parents worried.
Legislation for third-party testing of toys is being considered.
The recall highlights the need for stricter safety measures in the toy industry.
Mattel and RC2 are taking steps to address the lead paint problem.
